<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7062&amp;p=30405#p30405"><![CDATA[
Preferably any photo program that can zoom in enough to alter each pixel. <br />One that can work with, and export a transparent .png or transparent 32 bit alpha bitmap image.<br />Program needs to have a color picker, so exact pixel value can be set. <br />A pixel measurement ruler is handy too.<br /><br />Practically any Adobe image editor should work. Paint.Net, Gimp, PaintShopPro. <br />Splitwirez has his Paint.Net. Jcee with Gimp. Ivo-Adobe, Gaurav -?, others-?<br /><br />My favorite barebones editor is PixelFormer.<br />It can zoom in up to 6400%, making it easy to adjust the pixel line at top.<br />Adding an additional 1 pixel horizontal line should be easy in any program.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sat Nov 19, 2016 7:21 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
