<div class="quotetitle">TheOlderNe0 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Thanks for the comment 'juniper7'.......i was just trying to make some different &amp; entertaining start buttons which are not boring. The classic shell is highly customizable and everyone should make use of this ability. I really want to make some 'animated start buttons' but can't figure out how to animate some 15 or 30 frames.........how to add that single line of coloured pixels on top of that image???.........which software should i use 'photoshop' or 'Coraldraw' ?????........i am looking forward for some guidance..................Thanks once again <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /></div><br />Personally I'd recommend <a href="http://www.getpaint.net/index.html" class="postlink">paint.NET</a> , but I know some people here would probably disagree...<br /><br />EDIT: I should note that while paint.NET is an excellent image editor, it requires this plugin: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://forums.getpaint.net/index.php?/topic/11201-alpha-32bits-bitmap-support-for-paintnet/">http://forums.getpaint.net/index.php?/t ... -paintnet/</a><!-- m --> to export BMPs with transparency. (It exports them with the extension &quot;BMPX&quot;, so you'll need to rename them. Workflow is a bit awkward at times, but it's worth it IMO, for all the power paint.NET provides. Also, speaking of transparency, this may help you edit it: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://forums.getpaint.net/index.php?/topic/1854-alpha-mask-import-plugin-20/">http://forums.getpaint.net/index.php?/t ... plugin-20/</a><!-- m --> )<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9454">Splitwirez</a> — Sat Nov 19, 2016 6:32 am</p><hr />
